entries.femaleVariant: So, any thoughts?
Cop who saved Rhyne – who is he?
What's the Red Queen's Race?
Red Queen's Race – what is it?
Got me. Never heard of it, sorry.
Anyone else besides Rhyne's detail have access to the terminal?
Hmm… NCPD. That's it.
Cop who saved Rhyne – know anything about 'im?
Detective River Ward. Good guy. We worked a few cases together.
Who's Holt?
Rhyne's deputy. And his bulldog, so to speak. Running in Rhyne's place now.
Mayor's huscle – they NCPD?
No. All hand-picked by Holt and on a corp's payroll.
But there are ex-cops among them.
The conference, why was it held?
For no particular reason. Rhyne liked the sound of his voice and seeing himself on TV… Hehehe… Yeah, that sort of thing.
As far as I recall, the drop in Night City's violent crime rate was the excuse for this one. Rhyne came out to tout it.
Sorry – drop?
Rhyne reclassified Pacifica an "independent district." Stats for that part of town stopped counting.
Huh. Clever.
I'll call Ward.
Mayor's personal security also NCPD?
Who's Holt?
Who's got access to the security terminal?
What was the conference about?
You wanna talk to 'im, I'll put you in touch.
Sheesh. Ward had great timing.
Either has crazy good luck or had a source, got good info. I'm gonna need some of each.
Well said.
If you need anything else, let us know, we'll help.
Sending you his detes.
[Return shard] Too early to tell.
[Return shard] Think you might be onto something.
Rather not jump to any conclusions. That's not much to go on. Still too early to say.
Whole thing stinks worse than Coronado Bay in July.
Any questions at this point?
[Return shard] Pure coincidence, looks like.
Like a choom of mine says, I've seen stranger coincidences.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, like a choom of mine says, I've seen stranger coincidences.

entries.femaleVariant: Did you, uh, see anything suspicious, anything at all? Or are we paranoid?
Sure, sure.
Huh… So suspicions confirmed.
Hmm... Interesting. We felt differently, and strongly so.
Well, first impressions can at times be tricky.
[Get out]
